    <taskbody>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Highlight the text that you would like to add a note to.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click on the toolbar icon "Tag Note" or right-click on the text and choose
                        <cmdname>Tag Note</cmdname>. <image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Add38d995-c0cc-49ad-a750-a32eb9eb4558/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_zdy_yv2_np" align="center"/><image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Ac2c9d410-afb8-4a05-b0c0-d7969685505a/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_mwy_b4v_tp" align="center"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>A mini-editor will pop-up, enter any information that you would like in the
                    pop-up.</cmd>
                <info>There is a specific way to add text within tags in the mini-editor. To do
                    this, you click the tag twice in the structure/markup tree, so that its entry is
                    italicized (this means the tag's content is selected). you can then start
                    typing, which will add text content to that tag. <note>When using the
                        mini-editor you can add XML and RDF tags just like in the main editor,
                        though the toolbar options are limited (e.g. you cannot choose to "save" or
                        "validate" the note). The structure and entity panels on the left mimic the
                        structure panel in the editor and displays all the tags you added to the
                        note in the mini-editor.<image placement="break"
                            href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Ab5a17ed9-0790-4e4a-b7f9-dabc68e7caf3/datastream/OBJ/view"
                            id="image_vbk_24v_tp" align="center" height="4in" width="6in"
                    /></note></info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Once you have entered the text into the editor, you can begin to tag the
                    document. Adding structural tags and entities to the document. <image
                        placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Aef3182c6-65df-4f36-af9c-f0ac60739315/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_fpm_qw2_np" align="center" height="4in" width="6in"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>If/When you decide to add entities to your note, a "mini-editor" will
                        popup.<image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Aba443ffc-ad80-4e2c-b1ea-b4176dab9481/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_un2_sw2_np" align="center" height="4in" width="6in"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Once you have finished creating your note, click on <cmdname>Save</cmdname>.<image
                        placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A11fb457e-2f2a-4f33-af5f-4e55fd75d80f/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_ir3_nw2_np" align="center" height="4in" width="6in"/></cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
        <result>You have now created a note in your document. You can see in the image below that
